{"synckey":1686614624,"updated":[{"bookId":"3300029064","bookmarkId":"3300029064_5_1824-1913","createTime":1686614624,"chapterUid":5,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"在发达国家，而且在发展中国家也越来越如此，身份、政治、经济和环境在很大程度上是被“我们如何消费”塑造的。品位、外表和生活方式定义了我们是谁（或者想成为谁）及他人是如何看待我们的。","range":"1824-1913"},{"bookId":"3300029064","bookmarkId":"3300029064_5_675-751","createTime":1686614598,"chapterUid":5,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"在前现代的村庄里，大多数物品是作为礼物或是随嫁妆而传递得来的，与之相比，在现代社会里，物品主要是在市场上买来的。而且，它们在我们的生活中停留的时间更短。","range":"675-751"},{"bookId":"3300029064","bookmarkId":"3300029064_5_422-493","createTime":1686614562,"chapterUid":5,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"我们生活在一个被物品包围的世界中。一个典型的德国人拥有一万件物品。在洛杉矶，一个中产阶级家庭的车库里不再只是停放着一辆汽车，还放着数百箱杂物。","range":"422-493"},{"bookId":"3300029064","bookmarkId":"3300029064_3_859-889","createTime":1686614539,"chapterUid":3,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"学生同样应该被视为教育市场的消费者。消费者既是顾客，也是公民","range":"859-889"}],"removed":[],"chapters":[{"title":"导论","chapterUid":5,"chapterIdx":5},{"title":"致谢","chapterUid":3,"chapterIdx":3}],"book":{"bookId":"3300029064","version":1291872669,"format":"epub","soldout":0,"bookStatus":1,"cover":"https://cdn.weread.qq.com/weread/cover/93/cpPlatform_wwGKfYBVtWnkegFgE6aY3j/s_cpPlatform_wwGKfYBVtWnkegFgE6aY3j.jpg","title":"商品帝国：一部消费主义全球史","author":"弗兰克·特伦特曼","coverBoxInfo":{"blurhash":"KnK^yyofae00WBofRjkCa|","colors":[{"key":"1/4","hex":"#201b19"},{"key":"1/6","hex":"#201b19"},{"key":"1/8","hex":"#201b19"},{"key":"2/4","hex":"#34302e"},{"key":"2/6","hex":"#34302e"},{"key":"2/8","hex":"#34302e"},{"key":"3/4","hex":"#4c4744"},{"key":"3/6","hex":"#4c4744"},{"key":"3/8","hex":"#4c4744"},{"key":"3/12","hex":"#4c4744"},{"key":"4/6","hex":"#645f5c"},{"key":"4/10","hex":"#645f5c"},{"key":"4/4","hex":"#645f5c"},{"key":"5/10","hex":"#7e7975"},{"key":"5/4","hex":"#7e7975"},{"key":"5/8","hex":"#7e7975"},{"key":"6/4","hex":"#98928f"},{"key":"6/6","hex":"#98928f"},{"key":"6/8","hex":"#98928f"},{"key":"6/12","hex":"#98928f"},{"key":"7/8","hex":"#b2ada9"}